{
  "texts": [
    "During training, the DCGAN appears to have learned that these small-scale fluctuations are characteristic of realistic samples and therefore reproduces them in its generated outputs.The evaluation metrics support these qualitative impressions.",
    "Considering the near-wake region (see figure 11), comprising the first 25% of the total wake length, the VAE tends to locally underestimate the mean local velocity fluctuation magnitude and fails to fully capture the statistical variability associated with coherent and small-scale turbulence.",
    "For the 4V2H case, both DCGAN and DDPM closely match the VAE GAN DDPM Real statistical properties of the measured PIV data.",
    "The DCGAN performs particularly well in the lower wake region, where the flow exhibits a large, steady vortex with weak fluctuations.",
    "Nevertheless, in the second high-intensity turbulence region, the DDPM slightly outperforms the DCGAN."
  ]
}